<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the `sys_report` row that
    declares the "My Overdue Tasks" list report on the
    `x_casemgmt_case_task` custom table inside the scoped application
    `x_casemgmt`.

    Per AAP Section 0.5.1 (File-by-File Transformation Plan) verbatim:
        servicenow-case-management-poc/reports/x_casemgmt_my_overdue_tasks.xml
            CREATE  Source: -
            Key Changes: "List report: due_date < javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)
            AND status != Closed AND assigned_to = javascript:gs.getUserID()"

    Per AAP Section 0.4.1 (Refactored Structure Planning) verbatim:
        Agent Workspace Dashboard widget inventory includes
            "list widget for 'My overdue tasks'"

    Per AAP Section 0.4.4 (User Interface Design) verbatim:
        Agent Workspace Dashboard - "list widget for 'My overdue tasks'"

    Per AAP Section 0.7.3 (Validation Framework) verbatim, this report is
    one of the data sources for Gate 6 (Dashboards):
        "Both dashboards render with synthetic data ... All widgets display
         data; no broken report references"

    Per AAP Section 0.3.1 (Exhaustively In Scope) verbatim:
        servicenow-case-management-poc/reports/sys_report_x_casemgmt_my_overdue_tasks.xml
            "list of tasks where assigned_to = current user AND
             due_date < Today AND status != Closed"

    THIS FILE'S ROLE IN THE OVERALL POC
    ===================================
    This is the SOLE report among the eight `sys_report` records that
    queries `x_casemgmt_case_task`; the other seven all query
    `x_casemgmt_case`. The report is consumed by the Agent Workspace
    Dashboard (../dashboards/pa_dashboards_x_casemgmt_agent_workspace.xml)
    as a list widget. When rendered, each viewing user sees ONLY their
    own overdue tasks (per-viewer result-set semantics) - the dynamic
    `javascript:gs.getUserID()` substitution at evaluation time
    eliminates any need for hardcoded sys_user references.

    The "overdue" determination uses `javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)`,
    which evaluates to midnight (00:00:00) of "today" in the system
    timezone. Tasks with `due_date` strictly less than today's midnight
    are deemed overdue; tasks due "today" are NOT yet overdue under
    this rule. This semantic matches the AAP-verbatim rule
    (`due_date < javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)`) and intentionally
    favors the conservative interpretation - a task due at 5pm today
    will not be flagged overdue until tomorrow's midnight rolls over.

    SEMANTIC SOURCE-SIDE ANCHOR (READ-ONLY, NOT BYTE-FOR-BYTE PORTED)
    =================================================================
    ArkCase's task model is at
    acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-task-plugin/src/main/java/
    com/armedia/acm/plugins/task/model/AcmTask.java. The relevant
    fields for THIS report are (lines numbered against the source):

      - line 70-71:
            @NotNull
            private Date dueDate;
        ArkCase enforced not-null on the `dueDate` Bean Validation
        annotation. The ServiceNow target preserves this constraint
        via the Mandatory dictionary flag on `due_date` (defined in
        ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_task_due_date.xml).

      - line 75:
            private String assignee;
        ArkCase tracked the task assignee as a String field (typically
        an LDAP user-name). The ServiceNow target replaces this with a
        Reference field `assigned_to` -> sys_user (defined in
        ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_task_assigned_to.xml). The current
        viewer is matched against this reference via
        `javascript:gs.getUserID()`, which returns the viewer's
        sys_user.sys_id, eliminating the need for any string-matching
        on user-name.

      - line 81:
            private String status;
        ArkCase carried task status as a free-form String. The
        ServiceNow target normalizes this to a Choice field with
        exactly three values per AAP Section 0.5.7: "Open",
        "In Progress", "Closed" (defined in
        ../choices/sys_choice_case_task_status.xml). The encoded-query
        clause `status!=Closed` matches the Choice label byte-for-byte
        in Title Case.

      - line 68:
            @Size(min = 1)
            private String title;
        ArkCase's task `title` (Bean Validated @Size(min=1)) maps to
        the ServiceNow target's `subject` field per AAP Section 0.5.7
        (which lists `subject` as String(255) Mandatory on the task
        table). The report column shows the task subject as the first
        column for readability.

      - parent linkage:
            attachedToObjectType, attachedToObjectId
        ArkCase used a polymorphic owner-reference pattern with two
        fields (string type + numeric id). The ServiceNow target
        replaces this with a single typed Reference field `case` ->
        x_casemgmt_case (defined in ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_task_case.xml),
        which renders in list view as the case `number` (CASE0000001
        format) per AAP Section 0.7.4 (case display column = `number`).

    DESIGN DECISIONS LOCKED IN BY THIS FILE
    =======================================
      - Aggregation discipline (AAP Section 0.5.1, this report's row):
        type = list. Per agent-prompt Rule 5, list reports leave
        <aggregate/>, <aggregation_source/>, <group_by/> empty. The
        rendered output is one row per matching record (NOT a count
        or grouped tally).

      - Field-list discipline (agent-prompt Rule 6 verbatim):
        <field_list>subject,case,due_date,status</field_list>. Four
        columns, comma-separated, no spaces, in display order. The
        choice of NOT including `type` or `assigned_to` is intentional:
        - `type` is not required by the agent prompt; including it
          would add a column without operational value (the agent
          already knows their task workload type from context).
        - `assigned_to` is constant across all rows in this report
          (it is always the current viewer by virtue of the filter),
          so including it would be redundant and waste horizontal
          screen real-estate.
        - `priority` does NOT exist on x_casemgmt_case_task per AAP
          Section 0.5.7 (priority is a case-only field); attempting
          to reference it would produce a broken column.

      - Filter discipline (agent-prompt Rule 4 verbatim):
            assigned_to=javascript:gs.getUserID()
            ^due_date<javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0)
            ^status!=Closed
        Three encoded-query clauses, AND-joined by `^`. The `<`
        operator MUST be XML-escaped to `&lt;` in the serialized
        XML; failure to do so breaks Update Set XML deserialization
        and the "fresh PDI re-import" validation gate (AAP Section
        0.7.3 Gate 7) will produce a preview error.

      - Per-viewer semantics: the report is identical regardless of
        which user runs it; the platform's encoded-query parser
        substitutes `gs.getUserID()` at evaluation time, so each
        viewer sees only their own overdue tasks. This is the
        ServiceNow-native equivalent of a "personal queue" view
        without requiring per-user report duplication.

      - Date-window semantics: `gs.daysAgoStart(0)` returns midnight
        (00:00:00) of "today". The cutoff is strict less-than (`<`),
        not less-than-or-equal (`<=`). A task with `due_date` set to
        any time today is NOT yet overdue. A task with `due_date`
        set to yesterday at any time IS overdue. This conservative
        interpretation matches the AAP-specified semantics verbatim
        and avoids false-positive overdue flags during the day a
        task is due.

      - Scope binding: <sys_scope>x_casemgmt</sys_scope> and
        <sys_package source="x_casemgmt">x_casemgmt</sys_package>
        bind THIS record to the same scoped-app row that the parent
        sys_app record (../app/sys_app/x_casemgmt_case_management.xml)
        publishes. Cross-file consistency: the sibling sibling reports
        (e.g., x_casemgmt_avg_time_to_close.xml) use the identical
        scope-reference values, ensuring all eight reports resolve
        to the same sys_app row at preview time. Reference-by-name
        not reference-by-sys_id per AAP Section 0.7.2 (no hardcoded
        sys_ids constraint).

      - <sys_id> determinism: the value
        d9121344dff6c38d1db560bb7562f6d6 is the lowercase MD5 of the
        canonical identifier "sys_report.x_casemgmt_my_overdue_tasks".
        The MD5 input is the canonical record identifier
        <sys_class_name>.<name>, ensuring re-running this build with
        identical inputs produces an identical sys_id. This stability
        is REQUIRED because the Agent Workspace dashboard
        (../dashboards/pa_dashboards_x_casemgmt_agent_workspace.xml)
        references THIS report by name; if the sys_id were
        non-deterministic, two consecutive Update Set imports could
        produce divergent sys_ids on the same logical record,
        breaking the dashboard widget binding.

    CROSS-DEPENDENCY GRAPH
    ======================
    DEPENDS ON (must load earlier in the Update Set):
      - ../app/sys_app/x_casemgmt_case_management.xml
      - ../app/sys_scope/x_casemgmt.xml
      - ../tables/x_casemgmt_case_task.xml             (parent table)
      - ../tables/x_casemgmt_case.xml                  (referenced via `case` column)
      - ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_task_subject.xml
      - ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_task_case.xml
      - ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_task_due_date.xml
      - ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_task_status.xml
      - ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_task_assigned_to.xml
      - ../choices/sys_choice_case_task_status.xml    (defines `Closed` value)

    REFERENCED BY (must load later in the Update Set):
      - ../dashboards/pa_dashboards_x_casemgmt_agent_workspace.xml
        References THIS report by `<name>x_casemgmt_my_overdue_tasks</name>`,
        NOT by sys_id, so a fresh-PDI re-import correctly resolves the
        widget binding to whatever sys_id the platform assigns at import
        time (or, in our deterministic case, to the MD5-derived sys_id
        above).

    SEED-DATA DEPENDENCY (Validation Gate 6 pass condition):
      - ../seed-data/users/sys_user_x_casemgmt_demo_agent.xml must exist
        so that gs.getUserID() resolves to a real sys_user when the
        dashboard is run by the demo agent.
      - ../seed-data/tasks/x_casemgmt_case_task_demo_*.xml must include
        at least one task where:
          assigned_to = demo_agent (resolved by user_name lookup)
          due_date    = a date in the past (e.g., gs.daysAgoStart(7))
          status      = Open OR In Progress (NOT Closed)
        Without such a seed task, this report returns zero rows when
        rendered on the Agent Workspace dashboard, which would fail
        the "All widgets display data" criterion of Validation Gate 6
        (AAP Section 0.7.3) - even though the report DEFINITION itself
        is correct.

    UPDATE-SET ORDERING
    ===================
    Per AAP Section 0.5.2 (Cross-File Dependencies):
      - AFTER tables, dictionary, choices.
      - AFTER seed-data so that running the report yields non-empty
        results during validation.
      - BEFORE the Agent Workspace dashboard so that dashboard
        widget binding resolves.

    AUTHORING-RULES COMPLIANCE
    ==========================
      - AAP Section 0.7.2 verbatim:
          "No-hardcoded-sys_id constraint. Anywhere - flows, ACL
           conditions, scripts, seed data, UI Policies, UI Actions,
           Business Rules. Every cross-reference is resolved by
           GlideRecord lookup against a stable human-readable key
           (name, user_name, number, role_label)."
        This file: <sys_scope> and <sys_package> resolve by scope
        name; <sys_id> is THIS record's own primary key (not a
        hardcoded reference to another record). The `assigned_to`
        comparison uses gs.getUserID() (dynamic), not a literal
        sys_user.sys_id. All compliant.

      - AAP Section 0.7.2 verbatim:
          "No-PII constraint. Synthetic data only."
        This file: report definition contains no PII; the report
        merely SELECTS rows from a table. Whatever PII or non-PII
        data is in those rows is the seed-data agent's responsibility
        to keep synthetic. The report definition is PII-free.

      - AAP Section 0.7.2 verbatim:
          "Scope-namespace exclusivity: every artifact ... must live
           in the auto-assigned `x_casemgmt` namespace; zero global-
           scope writes are permitted."
        This file: <name> is `x_casemgmt_my_overdue_tasks`; <table>
        is `x_casemgmt_case_task`; <sys_scope> and <sys_package> bind
        to the scoped app. Zero global-scope writes.

      - AAP Section 0.7.4 verbatim:
          "Auto-numbering format: the case `number` field MUST use
           format `CASE0000001` (7-digit zero-padded) and be Read-only."
        This file: column 2 (`case`) renders the parent case's display
        column, which IS `number` (CASE0000001 format) per the
        x_casemgmt_case auto-numbering definition in
        ../numbers/sys_number_x_casemgmt_case.xml.

